The paper discusses information complexity, which is a field that deals with the amount of information that needs to be communicated between two parties to solve a problem. This topic is closely related to communication complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions circuit complexity, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper discusses the direct sum and direct product conjectures, which are related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
